
Documention is created in DocBook format, see http://docbook.org/

Html is generated using command:

cd luntbuild-doc/guide
xsltproc --nonet luntbuild-html.xsl luntbuild.docbook

cd luntbuild-doc/faq
xsltproc --nonet luntbuild-html.xsl faqs.docbook


Pdf is generated using command:

cd luntbuild-doc/guide
xsltproc --nonet luntbuild-pdf.xsl luntbuild.docbook

cd luntbuild-doc/faq
xsltproc --nonet luntbuild-pdf.xsl faqs.docbook


XSLT processor, where to get it.

On cygwin (http://www.cygwin.com) it is part of the cygwin docbook package:

The XSLT C library, DocBook XML DTD 4.2, XSL stylesheets for the DocBook XML DTD

On Linux you will need The XSLT C library package:

See: http://linux.about.com/library/cmd/blcmdl1_xsltproc.htm